---
description: On every user turn, proactively run failed-Run logging then fix agents
alwaysApply: true
---

# Failed Run loop (every prompt)

When the user message mentions a failed Run, Call failed, Error, FAILED,
connect timeout, SIP/TLS/RTP/STT/DTMF issue, lab dial problem, or pastes an
error from the desktop/UI:

1. **First** invoke the `run-failure-logger` subagent (Task tool,
   `subagent_type: run-failure-logger`) to ensure evidence-grade logs exist.
2. **Then** invoke the `run-failure-fixer` subagent (`subagent_type: run-failure-fixer`)
   to diagnose and fix using those logs.
3. If the turn is only "retry" / "launch" / status with no
 new error text, still
   check `.logs/desktop-relaunch.log` and Asterisk briefly; invoke the pair if a
   new failure appeared since last turn.

If Task/`run-failure-*` subagent types are unavailable in this session, perform
the same workflows yourself using `.cursor/agents/run-failure-logger.md` and
`.cursor/agents/run-failure-fixer.md` as the system prompts.

Do not skip this loop when the user pastes a call/Run error — even if the
request also asks for something else.